cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.LG 

This paper focuses on computational models for sarcasm detection in social media discussions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are a type of recurrent neural network (RNN) commonly used in NLP, suggesting cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as possible sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the differences between datasets, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper compares the results of the computational models with human performance, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
